EP  - 176
PY  - 1981
DA  - 1981/11/01/
SN  - 0304-4076
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-4076(81)90024-5
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304407681900245
AB  - The concept of Granger-causality is formulated for a finite-dimensional multiple time series. Special attention is given to causality patterns in autoregressive series, and it is shown how these patterns can be tested under quite general assumptions using a χ2 statistic. The power of the test is discussed, and it is shown that the χ2 statistic results from a Lagrange multiplier test in the Gaussian case. The causality test is tried both on artificial data and some economic time series. Finally we consider the problem of constrained estimation in models with a known causality structure.
